cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper deals with modelling sequences and temporal networks with dynamic community structures, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with temporal networks and their community structures, which are often studied in the context of social and information networks. 

cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the development of a data-driven method for modelling temporal networks, which could be relevant to software engineering. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a nonparametric Bayesian inference framework to identify the simplest model that can explain temporal interaction data, which is a common approach in machine learning. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with evolving complex systems and their dynamic interactions, which could be relevant to systems and control. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of methods to extract the temporal networks’ large-scale dynamic community structure, which could be relevant to data structures and algorithms.
